# Close session

`C-x` closes the selected live tmux session. The shortcut is only offered for
live tmux sessions, not repo-only entries.

    :bins jj tmux cat sleep

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', 'tmux', 'cat', and 'sleep' are available.

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :$ jj git init beta (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R beta -m "beta commit" (exit: 0)
    :t new-session -d -s alpha "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh cli -r beta; cat" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 120 -y 10 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0

The initial selection is the live `alpha` session, so the header offers close.

    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{6,8})\b/h"

```terminal
session:                                       ┃
  4/4 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close         ┃
▌⬤ alpha                                       ┃
 ⬤ runner                                      ┃
 ⬤ ui                                          ┃
   beta                                     bet┃
                                               ┃
                                               ┃
                                               ┃
                                               ┃
```

Filtering to the repo-only `beta` row hides the close shortcut.

    :k beta
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{6,8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: beta                                  ┃@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt hhhhhhhh
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-n] new           ┃│  (empty) beta commit
▌  beta                                     bet┃◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh
                                               ┃
                                               ┃
                                               ┃
                                               ┃
                                               ┃
                                               ┃
                                               ┃
```

Pressing `C-x` on the live `alpha` session should kill `alpha` and exit without
switching to it.

    :k C-u C-x
    :$ sleep 1 (exit: 0)
    :t has-session -t alpha (failure)

```
can't find session: alpha
```
    :t has-session -t ui (success)

